This paper deals with the problem of interference in LoRa networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI). The paper also discusses the use of directional antennae and multiple base stations to combat interference, which involves signal processing and information theory (IT). The simulation methodology used in the paper involves system modeling and control (SY). The paper also discusses the performance metrics used to evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed methods, which is related to multimedia (MM). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of interference in LoRa networks, which is related to cryptography (CR).
